sourceQuestion:
Consider the following pseudocode, where S is a semaphore initialized to 5 in line #2 and counter is a shared variable initialized to 0 in line #1. Assume that the increment operation in line #7 is NOT atomic.

1. int counter = 0;
2. Semaphore S = init(5);
3. void parop(void)
4. {
5.   wait(S);
6.   wait(S);
7.   counter++;
8.   signal(S);
9.   signal(S);
10. }

If 10 threads invoke parop concurrently, which of the following is a possible value of counter at the end of execution of all the threads?

A. 3
B. 5
C. 7
D. 9

